We would like to make a function which creates HTML blocks like:
  <B> => <b>{childen}</b>
Etc. for common HTML elements.

This can follow the design pattern of createStubBlock (see also src/components/componentMap.js). We would need to extend this so that the system knows which attributes to add. For example <Td> should probably include colspan and rowspan.

For now, we'd just like to include **common** HTML elements and attributes; the goal isn't to replicate all of HTML.

Do read the docs first, so you know what's going on!



